unspecifyIlm(25.10)                                        unspecifyIlm(25.10)

Name
       unspecifyIlm - Unspecifies the ILM cell

Syntax
       unspecifyIlm

       [-help]

       -cell <cellName>

       Unspecifies the ILM cell.

       This  is  used  to  unspecify a previously specified ILM. This would be
       useful in situations where ILMs are to be removed from the  design,  to
       put them in non-ILM or black box mode.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each unspecifyIlm parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man unspecifyIlm

       -cell <cellName>
              The name of the block to unspecify.

Related Information
              * specifyIlm

              * Top-level Timing Closure Methodologies chapter of Innovus User
                Guide.

